            "role": "assistant",
            "content": "{\"message\":\"Performing STRIDE-per-element threat modeling. Starting with External Entities. Identified threats for Developers/CI/CD and End Users/Clients based on Spoofing and Repudiation categories. This is the first part of the full report.\",\"threats\":[{\"id\":1,\"element\":\"Developers / CI/CD\",\"threat_description\":\"Unauthorized actor gains or reuses developer or pipeline credentials to impersonate legitimate provisioning.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"Mitre ATT&CK\":\"T1078: Valid Accounts\",\"OWASP Top 10\":\"A07: Identification and Authentication Failures\",\"mitigation\":\"Enforce strong MFA on developer accounts and CI/CD pipelines; rotate service principal keys; use managed identities.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H\"},{\"id\":2,\"element\":\"Developers / CI/CD\",\"threat_description\":\"Actions taken by developers or pipeline processes are not adequately logged, allowing repudiation of administrative changes.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"Mitre ATT&CK\":null,\"OWASP Top 10\":\"A09: Security Logging and Monitoring Failures\",\"mitigation\":\"Enable immutable, centralized audit logs for all Terraform and local-exec operations; correlate events to identities.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:N\"},{\"id\":3,\"element\":\"End Users / Clients\",\"threat_description\":\"Attacker spoofs legitimate client requests (e.g., forged JWTs or session tokens) to access function APIs.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"Mitre ATT&CK\":\"T1078: Valid Accounts\",\"OWASP Top 10\":\"A07: Identification and Authentication Failures\",\"mitigation\":\"Validate and verify JWT tokens server-side; implement token expiration and audience restrictions; enable OAuth scopes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H\"},{\"id\":4,\"element\":\"End Users / Clients\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of non-repudiation on API calls allows malicious clients to deny their actions or evade accountability.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"Mitre ATT&CK\":null,\"OWASP Top 10\":\"A09: Security Logging and Monitoring Failures\",\"mitigation\":\"Implement request logging with immutable IDs, timestamps, and origin metadata; integrate WAF or API gateway logs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:N\"}],\"is_final\":false}"
